title: Oregon State-bound Zach Reichle of Wilsonville scores 56: Where it ranks among Oregon games since 2000
text:
Share WILSONVILLE'S ZACH REICHLE SCORES 56: WHERE IT RANKS SINCE 2000 
Wilsonville forward Zach Reichle had the game of the year to date Tuesday night, pouring in 56 points in the No. 1 Wildcats' 89-47 win over Milwaukie. Reichle did it efficiently, hitting 20 of 25 shots, including 9 of 13 from 3-point range. Reichle also had eight rebounds, six assists and five steals, and went 7 of 7 from the free throw line. 
Billy Gates | The Oregonian/OregonLive ZACH REICHLE POURS IN 56 IN WILSONVILLE VICTORY 
Said Wilsonville coach Chris Roche of the 6-5, Oregon State-bound forward: "It's not like he came out and fired 35-40 shots to get his points. He actually did it totally within the team flow of the game... well, until he really got going, then all bets were off and he was attacking. Zebo was amazing tonight, and that was fun to watch."
